{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"alias":"sue-peer-twin","description":"# Live eval solver: context-injection + repo-tool stubbing + fixture corpus (2.2 + 2.4)\n\n## What\n\nThe 3 reviewers are store+repo-coupled agentic ops (verify_completion reads the store\n+ has a show_ticket tool; review_ticket steers the agent over the repo via\nlist_directory/search_files/read_file; scan_spec fetches+batches epics), so they\ncannot consume inline prose. Build the eval-time solver that makes them runnable\ndeterministically:\n- inject synthetic ticket/graph context in place of the store fetch;\n- provide a stubbed or fixture-backed repo for the file tools;\n- a small per-case fixture corpus so completion-verifier FAIL findings can satisfy\n  the source-citation contract; adjudicate ground-truth labels (define labeler/consensus;\n  seed labels provisional per the existing eval README convention).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] An eval solver injects per-case ticket/graph context + stubs the agentic file tools (no live store/repo dependency).\n- [ ] A versioned fixture corpus backs the cases that need repo state (esp. completion-verifier citations).\n- [ ] Ground-truth labels are adjudicated and recorded; seed labels marked provisional.\n- [ ] Tests exercise the solver against FakeRunner/FakeAgentRunner (offline, no tokens).","id":"7402-ddbf-bfbc-415a","parent_id":"b4af-6782-0f12-4a1d","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"task","title":"Live eval solver: context-injection + tool stubbing + fixtures (2.2+2.4)"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1782578572614846001,"uuid":"e9725afd-a907-4043-abd0-26ad966ef322"}